{"paragraphs":[{"cues":[{"time":0,"text":"18 minutes is an absolutely brutal time limit,"},{"time":2000,"text":"so I'm going to dive straight in, right at the point"},{"time":4000,"text":"where I get this thing to work."},{"time":6000,"text":"Here we go. I'm going to talk about five different things."},{"time":8000,"text":"I'm going to talk about why defeating aging is desirable."},{"time":11000,"text":"I'm going to talk about why we have to get our shit together,"},{"time":13000,"text":"and actually talk about this a bit more than we do."},{"time":15000,"text":"I'm going to talk about feasibility as well, of course."},{"time":17000,"text":"I'm going to talk about why we are so fatalistic"},{"time":19000,"text":"about doing anything about aging."},{"time":21000,"text":"And then I'm going spend perhaps the second half of the talk"},{"time":23000,"text":"talking about, you know, how we might actually be able to prove that fatalism is wrong,"},{"time":28000,"text":"namely, by actually doing something about it."}]},{"cues":[{"time":30000,"text":"I'm going to do that in two steps."},{"time":32000,"text":"The first one I'm going to talk about is"},{"time":34000,"text":"how to get from a relatively modest amount of life extension --"},{"time":37000,"text":"which I'm going to define as 30 years, applied to people"},{"time":40000,"text":"who are already in middle-age when you start --"},{"time":42000,"text":"to a point which can genuinely be called defeating aging."},{"time":45000,"text":"Namely, essentially an elimination of the relationship between"},{"time":49000,"text":"how old you are and how likely you are to die in the next year --"},{"time":51000,"text":"or indeed, to get sick in the first place."},{"time":53000,"text":"And of course, the last thing I'm going to talk about"},{"time":55000,"text":"is how to reach that intermediate step,"},{"time":57000,"text":"that point of maybe 30 years life extension."}]},{"cues":[{"time":60000,"text":"So I'm going to start with why we should."},{"time":63000,"text":"Now, I want to ask a question."},{"time":65000,"text":"Hands up: anyone in the audience who is in favor of malaria?"},{"time":68000,"text":"That was easy. OK."},{"time":69000,"text":"OK. Hands up: anyone in the audience"},{"time":71000,"text":"who's not sure whether malaria is a good thing or a bad thing?"},{"time":74000,"text":"OK. So we all think malaria is a bad thing."},{"time":76000,"text":"That's very good news, because I thought that was what the answer would be."},{"time":78000,"text":"Now the thing is, I would like to put it to you"},{"time":80000,"text":"that the main reason why we think that malaria is a bad thing"},{"time":83000,"text":"is because of a characteristic of malaria that it shares with aging."},{"time":87000,"text":"And here is that characteristic."},{"time":90000,"text":"The only real difference is that aging kills considerably more people than malaria does."}]},{"cues":[{"time":95000,"text":"Now, I like in an audience, in Britain especially,"},{"time":97000,"text":"to talk about the comparison with foxhunting,"},{"time":99000,"text":"which is something that was banned after a long struggle,"},{"time":102000,"text":"by the government not very many months ago."},{"time":105000,"text":"I mean, I know I'm with a sympathetic audience here,"},{"time":107000,"text":"but, as we know, a lot of people are not entirely persuaded by this logic."},{"time":110000,"text":"And this is actually a rather good comparison, it seems to me."},{"time":113000,"text":"You know, a lot of people said, \"Well, you know,"},{"time":115000,"text":"city boys have no business telling us rural types what to do with our time."},{"time":120000,"text":"It's a traditional part of the way of life,"},{"time":122000,"text":"and we should be allowed to carry on doing it."},{"time":124000,"text":"It's ecologically sound; it stops the population explosion of foxes.\""},{"time":127000,"text":"But ultimately, the government prevailed in the end,"},{"time":129000,"text":"because the majority of the British public,"},{"time":130000,"text":"and certainly the majority of members of Parliament,"},{"time":132000,"text":"came to the conclusion that it was really something"},{"time":134000,"text":"that should not be tolerated in a civilized society."}]},{"cues":[{"time":136000,"text":"And I think that human aging shares"},{"time":137000,"text":"all of these characteristics in spades."},{"time":140000,"text":"What part of this do people not understand?"},{"time":142000,"text":"It's not just about life, of course --"},{"time":144000,"text":"(Laughter) --"},{"time":145000,"text":"it's about healthy life, you know --"},{"time":148000,"text":"getting frail and miserable and dependent is no fun,"},{"time":151000,"text":"whether or not dying may be fun."},{"time":153000,"text":"So really, this is how I would like to describe it."},{"time":155000,"text":"It's a global trance."},{"time":157000,"text":"These are the sorts of unbelievable excuses"},{"time":159000,"text":"that people give for aging."},{"time":161000,"text":"And, I mean, OK, I'm not actually saying"},{"time":163000,"text":"that these excuses are completely valueless."},{"time":165000,"text":"There are some good points to be made here,"},{"time":167000,"text":"things that we ought to be thinking about, forward planning"},{"time":170000,"text":"so that nothing goes too -- well, so that we minimize"},{"time":172000,"text":"the turbulence when we actually figure out how to fix aging."}]},{"cues":[{"time":175000,"text":"But these are completely crazy, when you actually"},{"time":178000,"text":"remember your sense of proportion."},{"time":180000,"text":"You know, these are arguments; these are things that"},{"time":184000,"text":"would be legitimate to be concerned about."},{"time":186000,"text":"But the question is, are they so dangerous --"},{"time":189000,"text":"these risks of doing something about aging --"},{"time":191000,"text":"that they outweigh the downside of doing the opposite,"},{"time":195000,"text":"namely, leaving aging as it is?"},{"time":197000,"text":"Are these so bad that they outweigh"},{"time":199000,"text":"condemning 100,000 people a day to an unnecessarily early death?"},{"time":205000,"text":"You know, if you haven't got an argument that's that strong,"},{"time":207000,"text":"then just don't waste my time, is what I say."},{"time":210000,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":211000,"text":"Now, there is one argument"},{"time":212000,"text":"that some people do think really is that strong, and here it is."},{"time":214000,"text":"People worry about overpopulation; they say,"},{"time":216000,"text":"\"Well, if we fix aging, no one's going to die to speak of,"},{"time":218000,"text":"or at least the death toll is going to be much lower,"},{"time":221000,"text":"only from crossing St. Giles carelessly."},{"time":223000,"text":"And therefore, we're not going to be able to have many kids,"},{"time":225000,"text":"and kids are really important to most people.\""},{"time":227000,"text":"And that's true."},{"time":229000,"text":"And you know, a lot of people try to fudge this question,"},{"time":232000,"text":"and give answers like this."},{"time":233000,"text":"I don't agree with those answers. I think they basically don't work."},{"time":236000,"text":"I think it's true, that we will face a dilemma in this respect."},{"time":239000,"text":"We will have to decide whether to have a low birth rate,"},{"time":243000,"text":"or a high death rate."},{"time":245000,"text":"A high death rate will, of course, arise from simply rejecting these therapies,"},{"time":248000,"text":"in favor of carrying on having a lot of kids."}]},{"cues":[{"time":252000,"text":"And, I say that that's fine --"},{"time":254000,"text":"the future of humanity is entitled to make that choice."},{"time":257000,"text":"What's not fine is for us to make that choice on behalf of the future."},{"time":261000,"text":"If we vacillate, hesitate,"},{"time":263000,"text":"and do not actually develop these therapies,"},{"time":266000,"text":"then we are condemning a whole cohort of people --"},{"time":270000,"text":"who would have been young enough and healthy enough"},{"time":272000,"text":"to benefit from those therapies, but will not be,"},{"time":274000,"text":"because we haven't developed them as quickly as we could --"},{"time":276000,"text":"we'll be denying those people an indefinite life span,"},{"time":278000,"text":"and I consider that that is immoral."},{"time":280000,"text":"That's my answer to the overpopulation question."}]},{"cues":[{"time":283000,"text":"Right. So the next thing is,"},{"time":285000,"text":"now why should we get a little bit more active on this?"},{"time":287000,"text":"And the fundamental answer is that"},{"time":289000,"text":"the pro-aging trance is not as dumb as it looks."},{"time":292000,"text":"It's actually a sensible way of coping with the inevitability of aging."},{"time":296000,"text":"Aging is ghastly, but it's inevitable, so, you know,"},{"time":300000,"text":"we've got to find some way to put it out of our minds,"},{"time":302000,"text":"and it's rational to do anything that we might want to do, to do that."},{"time":306000,"text":"Like, for example, making up these ridiculous reasons"},{"time":309000,"text":"why aging is actually a good thing after all."},{"time":311000,"text":"But of course, that only works when we have both of these components."},{"time":315000,"text":"And as soon as the inevitability bit becomes a little bit unclear --"},{"time":318000,"text":"and we might be in range of doing something about aging --"},{"time":320000,"text":"this becomes part of the problem."},{"time":322000,"text":"This pro-aging trance is what stops us from agitating about these things."},{"time":326000,"text":"And that's why we have to really talk about this a lot --"},{"time":330000,"text":"evangelize, I will go so far as to say, quite a lot --"},{"time":332000,"text":"in order to get people's attention, and make people realize"},{"time":335000,"text":"that they are in a trance in this regard."},{"time":337000,"text":"So that's all I'm going to say about that."}]},{"cues":[{"time":339000,"text":"I'm now going to talk about feasibility."},{"time":342000,"text":"And the fundamental reason, I think, why we feel that aging is inevitable"},{"time":346000,"text":"is summed up in a definition of aging that I'm giving here."},{"time":349000,"text":"A very simple definition."},{"time":350000,"text":"Aging is a side effect of being alive in the first place,"},{"time":353000,"text":"which is to say, metabolism."},{"time":355000,"text":"This is not a completely tautological statement;"},{"time":358000,"text":"it's a reasonable statement."},{"time":359000,"text":"Aging is basically a process that happens to inanimate objects like cars,"},{"time":363000,"text":"and it also happens to us,"},{"time":365000,"text":"despite the fact that we have a lot of clever self-repair mechanisms,"},{"time":368000,"text":"because those self-repair mechanisms are not perfect."}]},{"cues":[{"time":370000,"text":"So basically, metabolism, which is defined as"},{"time":372000,"text":"basically everything that keeps us alive from one day to the next,"},{"time":375000,"text":"has side effects."},{"time":377000,"text":"Those side effects accumulate and eventually cause pathology."},{"time":379000,"text":"That's a fine definition. So we can put it this way:"},{"time":381000,"text":"we can say that, you know, we have this chain of events."},{"time":383000,"text":"And there are really two games in town,"},{"time":385000,"text":"according to most people, with regard to postponing aging."},{"time":388000,"text":"They're what I'm calling here the \"gerontology approach\" and the \"geriatrics approach.\""},{"time":392000,"text":"The geriatrician will intervene late in the day,"},{"time":394000,"text":"when pathology is becoming evident,"},{"time":396000,"text":"and the geriatrician will try and hold back the sands of time,"},{"time":399000,"text":"and stop the accumulation of side effects"},{"time":402000,"text":"from causing the pathology quite so soon."},{"time":404000,"text":"Of course, it's a very short-term-ist strategy; it's a losing battle,"},{"time":407000,"text":"because the things that are causing the pathology"},{"time":410000,"text":"are becoming more abundant as time goes on."}]},{"cues":[{"time":412000,"text":"The gerontology approach looks much more promising on the surface,"},{"time":416000,"text":"because, you know, prevention is better than cure."},{"time":419000,"text":"But unfortunately the thing is that we don't understand metabolism very well."},{"time":422000,"text":"In fact, we have a pitifully poor understanding of how organisms work --"},{"time":425000,"text":"even cells we're not really too good on yet."},{"time":427000,"text":"We've discovered things like, for example,"},{"time":429000,"text":"RNA interference only a few years ago,"},{"time":432000,"text":"and this is a really fundamental component of how cells work."},{"time":434000,"text":"Basically, gerontology is a fine approach in the end,"},{"time":437000,"text":"but it is not an approach whose time has come"},{"time":439000,"text":"when we're talking about intervention."},{"time":441000,"text":"So then, what do we do about that?"},{"time":444000,"text":"I mean, that's a fine logic, that sounds pretty convincing,"},{"time":446000,"text":"pretty ironclad, doesn't it?"}]},{"cues":[{"time":448000,"text":"But it isn't."},{"time":450000,"text":"Before I tell you why it isn't, I'm going to go a little bit"},{"time":453000,"text":"into what I'm calling step two."},{"time":455000,"text":"Just suppose, as I said, that we do acquire --"},{"time":459000,"text":"let's say we do it today for the sake of argument --"},{"time":461000,"text":"the ability to confer 30 extra years of healthy life"},{"time":465000,"text":"on people who are already in middle age, let's say 55."},{"time":468000,"text":"I'm going to call that \"robust human rejuvenation.\" OK."},{"time":471000,"text":"What would that actually mean"},{"time":472000,"text":"for how long people of various ages today --"},{"time":475000,"text":"or equivalently, of various ages at the time that these therapies arrive --"},{"time":479000,"text":"would actually live?"},{"time":481000,"text":"In order to answer that question -- you might think it's simple,"},{"time":483000,"text":"but it's not simple."},{"time":484000,"text":"We can't just say, \"Well, if they're young enough to benefit from these therapies,"},{"time":487000,"text":"then they'll live 30 years longer.\""},{"time":488000,"text":"That's the wrong answer."},{"time":490000,"text":"And the reason it's the wrong answer is because of progress."}]},{"cues":[{"time":492000,"text":"There are two sorts of technological progress really,"},{"time":494000,"text":"for this purpose."},{"time":495000,"text":"There are fundamental, major breakthroughs,"},{"time":498000,"text":"and there are incremental refinements of those breakthroughs."},{"time":502000,"text":"Now, they differ a great deal"},{"time":504000,"text":"in terms of the predictability of time frames."},{"time":507000,"text":"Fundamental breakthroughs:"},{"time":508000,"text":"very hard to predict how long it's going to take"},{"time":510000,"text":"to make a fundamental breakthrough."},{"time":511000,"text":"It was a very long time ago that we decided that flying would be fun,"},{"time":514000,"text":"and it took us until 1903 to actually work out how to do it."},{"time":517000,"text":"But after that, things were pretty steady and pretty uniform."},{"time":521000,"text":"I think this is a reasonable sequence of events that happened"},{"time":524000,"text":"in the progression of the technology of powered flight."},{"time":528000,"text":"We can think, really, that each one is sort of"},{"time":532000,"text":"beyond the imagination of the inventor of the previous one, if you like."},{"time":535000,"text":"The incremental advances have added up to something"},{"time":539000,"text":"which is not incremental anymore."}]},{"cues":[{"time":541000,"text":"This is the sort of thing you see after a fundamental breakthrough."},{"time":544000,"text":"And you see it in all sorts of technologies."},{"time":546000,"text":"Computers: you can look at a more or less parallel time line,"},{"time":549000,"text":"happening of course a bit later."},{"time":550000,"text":"You can look at medical care. I mean, hygiene, vaccines, antibiotics --"},{"time":553000,"text":"you know, the same sort of time frame."},{"time":555000,"text":"So I think that actually step two, that I called a step a moment ago,"},{"time":559000,"text":"isn't a step at all."},{"time":560000,"text":"That in fact, the people who are young enough"},{"time":563000,"text":"to benefit from these first therapies"},{"time":565000,"text":"that give this moderate amount of life extension,"},{"time":567000,"text":"even though those people are already middle-aged when the therapies arrive,"},{"time":571000,"text":"will be at some sort of cusp."},{"time":573000,"text":"They will mostly survive long enough to receive improved treatments"},{"time":577000,"text":"that will give them a further 30 or maybe 50 years."},{"time":579000,"text":"In other words, they will be staying ahead of the game."},{"time":582000,"text":"The therapies will be improving faster than"},{"time":585000,"text":"the remaining imperfections in the therapies are catching up with us."}]},{"cues":[{"time":589000,"text":"This is a very important point for me to get across."},{"time":591000,"text":"Because, you know, most people, when they hear"},{"time":593000,"text":"that I predict that a lot of people alive today are going to live to 1,000 or more,"},{"time":598000,"text":"they think that I'm saying that we're going to invent therapies in the next few decades"},{"time":602000,"text":"that are so thoroughly eliminating aging"},{"time":605000,"text":"that those therapies will let us live to 1,000 or more."},{"time":608000,"text":"I'm not saying that at all."},{"time":610000,"text":"I'm saying that the rate of improvement of those therapies"},{"time":612000,"text":"will be enough."},{"time":613000,"text":"They'll never be perfect, but we'll be able to fix the things"},{"time":616000,"text":"that 200-year-olds die of, before we have any 200-year-olds."},{"time":619000,"text":"And the same for 300 and 400 and so on."},{"time":621000,"text":"I decided to give this a little name,"},{"time":624000,"text":"which is \"longevity escape velocity.\""},{"time":626000,"text":"(Laughter)"},{"time":628000,"text":"Well, it seems to get the point across."}]},{"cues":[{"time":631000,"text":"So, these trajectories here are basically how we would expect people to live,"},{"time":636000,"text":"in terms of remaining life expectancy,"},{"time":638000,"text":"as measured by their health,"},{"time":640000,"text":"for given ages that they were at the time that these therapies arrive."},{"time":643000,"text":"If you're already 100, or even if you're 80 --"},{"time":645000,"text":"and an average 80-year-old,"},{"time":647000,"text":"we probably can't do a lot for you with these therapies,"},{"time":649000,"text":"because you're too close to death's door"},{"time":651000,"text":"for the really initial, experimental therapies to be good enough for you."},{"time":655000,"text":"You won't be able to withstand them."},{"time":656000,"text":"But if you're only 50, then there's a chance"},{"time":658000,"text":"that you might be able to pull out of the dive and, you know --"},{"time":661000,"text":"(Laughter) --"},{"time":662000,"text":"eventually get through this"},{"time":665000,"text":"and start becoming biologically younger in a meaningful sense,"},{"time":668000,"text":"in terms of your youthfulness, both physical and mental,"},{"time":670000,"text":"and in terms of your risk of death from age-related causes."},{"time":672000,"text":"And of course, if you're a bit younger than that,"},{"time":674000,"text":"then you're never really even going"},{"time":676000,"text":"to get near to being fragile enough to die of age-related causes."}]},{"cues":[{"time":679000,"text":"So this is a genuine conclusion that I come to, that the first 150-year-old --"},{"time":684000,"text":"we don't know how old that person is today,"},{"time":686000,"text":"because we don't know how long it's going to take"},{"time":688000,"text":"to get these first-generation therapies."},{"time":690000,"text":"But irrespective of that age,"},{"time":692000,"text":"I'm claiming that the first person to live to 1,000 --"},{"time":696000,"text":"subject of course, to, you know, global catastrophes --"},{"time":699000,"text":"is actually, probably, only about 10 years younger than the first 150-year-old."},{"time":703000,"text":"And that's quite a thought."}]},{"cues":[{"time":705000,"text":"Alright, so finally I'm going to spend the rest of the talk,"},{"time":708000,"text":"my last seven-and-a-half minutes, on step one;"},{"time":711000,"text":"namely, how do we actually get to this moderate amount of life extension"},{"time":716000,"text":"that will allow us to get to escape velocity?"},{"time":719000,"text":"And in order to do that, I need to talk about mice a little bit."},{"time":723000,"text":"I have a corresponding milestone to robust human rejuvenation."},{"time":726000,"text":"I'm calling it \"robust mouse rejuvenation,\" not very imaginatively."},{"time":729000,"text":"And this is what it is."},{"time":731000,"text":"I say we're going to take a long-lived strain of mouse,"},{"time":733000,"text":"which basically means mice that live about three years on average."},{"time":736000,"text":"We do exactly nothing to them until they're already two years old."},{"time":739000,"text":"And then we do a whole bunch of stuff to them,"},{"time":741000,"text":"and with those therapies, we get them to live,"},{"time":743000,"text":"on average, to their fifth birthday."},{"time":745000,"text":"So, in other words, we add two years --"},{"time":747000,"text":"we treble their remaining lifespan,"},{"time":749000,"text":"starting from the point that we started the therapies."}]},{"cues":[{"time":751000,"text":"The question then is, what would that actually mean for the time frame"},{"time":754000,"text":"until we get to the milestone I talked about earlier for humans?"},{"time":757000,"text":"Which we can now, as I've explained,"},{"time":759000,"text":"equivalently call either robust human rejuvenation or longevity escape velocity."},{"time":763000,"text":"Secondly, what does it mean for the public's perception"},{"time":766000,"text":"of how long it's going to take for us to get to those things,"},{"time":768000,"text":"starting from the time we get the mice?"},{"time":770000,"text":"And thirdly, the question is, what will it do"},{"time":772000,"text":"to actually how much people want it?"},{"time":774000,"text":"And it seems to me that the first question"},{"time":776000,"text":"is entirely a biology question,"},{"time":777000,"text":"and it's extremely hard to answer."},{"time":779000,"text":"One has to be very speculative,"},{"time":781000,"text":"and many of my colleagues would say that we should not do this speculation,"},{"time":784000,"text":"that we should simply keep our counsel until we know more."}]},{"cues":[{"time":788000,"text":"I say that's nonsense."},{"time":789000,"text":"I say we absolutely are irresponsible if we stay silent on this."},{"time":792000,"text":"We need to give our best guess as to the time frame,"},{"time":795000,"text":"in order to give people a sense of proportion"},{"time":798000,"text":"so that they can assess their priorities."},{"time":800000,"text":"So, I say that we have a 50/50 chance"},{"time":803000,"text":"of reaching this RHR milestone,"},{"time":805000,"text":"robust human rejuvenation, within 15 years from the point"},{"time":808000,"text":"that we get to robust mouse rejuvenation."},{"time":810000,"text":"15 years from the robust mouse."},{"time":813000,"text":"The public's perception will probably be somewhat better than that."},{"time":816000,"text":"The public tends to underestimate how difficult scientific things are."},{"time":818000,"text":"So they'll probably think it's five years away."},{"time":820000,"text":"They'll be wrong, but that actually won't matter too much."},{"time":822000,"text":"And finally, of course, I think it's fair to say"},{"time":825000,"text":"that a large part of the reason why the public is so ambivalent about aging now"},{"time":829000,"text":"is the global trance I spoke about earlier, the coping strategy."},{"time":831000,"text":"That will be history at this point,"},{"time":833000,"text":"because it will no longer be possible to believe that aging is inevitable in humans,"},{"time":836000,"text":"since it's been postponed so very effectively in mice."},{"time":839000,"text":"So we're likely to end up with a very strong change in people's attitudes,"},{"time":843000,"text":"and of course that has enormous implications."}]},{"cues":[{"time":846000,"text":"So in order to tell you now how we're going to get these mice,"},{"time":849000,"text":"I'm going to add a little bit to my description of aging."},{"time":851000,"text":"I'm going to use this word \"damage\""},{"time":853000,"text":"to denote these intermediate things that are caused by metabolism"},{"time":857000,"text":"and that eventually cause pathology."},{"time":859000,"text":"Because the critical thing about this"},{"time":861000,"text":"is that even though the damage only eventually causes pathology,"},{"time":863000,"text":"the damage itself is caused ongoing-ly throughout life, starting before we're born."},{"time":868000,"text":"But it is not part of metabolism itself."},{"time":871000,"text":"And this turns out to be useful."},{"time":872000,"text":"Because we can re-draw our original diagram this way."},{"time":875000,"text":"We can say that, fundamentally, the difference between gerontology and geriatrics"},{"time":878000,"text":"is that gerontology tries to inhibit the rate"},{"time":880000,"text":"at which metabolism lays down this damage."},{"time":882000,"text":"And I'm going to explain exactly what damage is"},{"time":884000,"text":"in concrete biological terms in a moment."},{"time":887000,"text":"And geriatricians try to hold back the sands of time"},{"time":889000,"text":"by stopping the damage converting into pathology."},{"time":891000,"text":"And the reason it's a losing battle"},{"time":893000,"text":"is because the damage is continuing to accumulate."}]},{"cues":[{"time":895000,"text":"So there's a third approach, if we look at it this way."},{"time":898000,"text":"We can call it the \"engineering approach,\""},{"time":900000,"text":"and I claim that the engineering approach is within range."},{"time":903000,"text":"The engineering approach does not intervene in any processes."},{"time":906000,"text":"It does not intervene in this process or this one."},{"time":908000,"text":"And that's good because it means that it's not a losing battle,"},{"time":911000,"text":"and it's something that we are within range of being able to do,"},{"time":914000,"text":"because it doesn't involve improving on evolution."},{"time":917000,"text":"The engineering approach simply says,"},{"time":919000,"text":"\"Let's go and periodically repair all of these various types of damage --"},{"time":923000,"text":"not necessarily repair them completely, but repair them quite a lot,"},{"time":927000,"text":"so that we keep the level of damage down below the threshold"},{"time":930000,"text":"that must exist, that causes it to be pathogenic.\""},{"time":933000,"text":"We know that this threshold exists,"},{"time":935000,"text":"because we don't get age-related diseases until we're in middle age,"},{"time":938000,"text":"even though the damage has been accumulating since before we were born."}]},{"cues":[{"time":941000,"text":"Why do I say that we're in range? Well, this is basically it."},{"time":945000,"text":"The point about this slide is actually the bottom."},{"time":948000,"text":"If we try to say which bits of metabolism are important for aging,"},{"time":951000,"text":"we will be here all night, because basically all of metabolism"},{"time":954000,"text":"is important for aging in one way or another."},{"time":956000,"text":"This list is just for illustration; it is incomplete."},{"time":959000,"text":"The list on the right is also incomplete."},{"time":961000,"text":"It's a list of types of pathology that are age-related,"},{"time":964000,"text":"and it's just an incomplete list."},{"time":966000,"text":"But I would like to claim to you that this list in the middle is actually complete --"},{"time":969000,"text":"this is the list of types of thing that qualify as damage,"},{"time":972000,"text":"side effects of metabolism that cause pathology in the end,"},{"time":975000,"text":"or that might cause pathology."},{"time":977000,"text":"And there are only seven of them."},{"time":980000,"text":"They're categories of things, of course, but there's only seven of them."},{"time":983000,"text":"Cell loss, mutations in chromosomes, mutations in the mitochondria and so on."}]},{"cues":[{"time":988000,"text":"First of all, I'd like to give you an argument for why that list is complete."},{"time":993000,"text":"Of course one can make a biological argument."},{"time":995000,"text":"One can say, \"OK, what are we made of?\""},{"time":997000,"text":"We're made of cells and stuff between cells."},{"time":999000,"text":"What can damage accumulate in?"},{"time":1002000,"text":"The answer is: long-lived molecules,"},{"time":1004000,"text":"because if a short-lived molecule undergoes damage, but then the molecule is destroyed --"},{"time":1007000,"text":"like by a protein being destroyed by proteolysis -- then the damage is gone, too."},{"time":1011000,"text":"It's got to be long-lived molecules."},{"time":1013000,"text":"So, these seven things were all under discussion in gerontology a long time ago"},{"time":1016000,"text":"and that is pretty good news, because it means that,"},{"time":1020000,"text":"you know, we've come a long way in biology in these 20 years,"},{"time":1022000,"text":"so the fact that we haven't extended this list"},{"time":1024000,"text":"is a pretty good indication that there's no extension to be done."},{"time":1028000,"text":"However, it's better than that; we actually know how to fix them all,"},{"time":1030000,"text":"in mice, in principle -- and what I mean by in principle is,"},{"time":1033000,"text":"we probably can actually implement these fixes within a decade."},{"time":1036000,"text":"Some of them are partially implemented already, the ones at the top."}]},{"cues":[{"time":1040000,"text":"I haven't got time to go through them at all, but"},{"time":1043000,"text":"my conclusion is that, if we can actually get suitable funding for this,"},{"time":1047000,"text":"then we can probably develop robust mouse rejuvenation in only 10 years,"},{"time":1051000,"text":"but we do need to get serious about it."},{"time":1054000,"text":"We do need to really start trying."},{"time":1056000,"text":"So of course, there are some biologists in the audience,"},{"time":1059000,"text":"and I want to give some answers to some of the questions that you may have."},{"time":1062000,"text":"You may have been dissatisfied with this talk,"},{"time":1064000,"text":"but fundamentally you have to go and read this stuff."},{"time":1066000,"text":"I've published a great deal on this;"},{"time":1068000,"text":"I cite the experimental work on which my optimism is based,"},{"time":1071000,"text":"and there's quite a lot of detail there."},{"time":1073000,"text":"The detail is what makes me confident"},{"time":1075000,"text":"of my rather aggressive time frames that I'm predicting here."},{"time":1077000,"text":"So if you think that I'm wrong,"},{"time":1079000,"text":"you'd better damn well go and find out why you think I'm wrong."}]},{"cues":[{"time":1083000,"text":"And of course the main thing is that you shouldn't trust people"},{"time":1086000,"text":"who call themselves gerontologists because,"},{"time":1088000,"text":"as with any radical departure from previous thinking within a particular field,"},{"time":1092000,"text":"you know, you expect people in the mainstream to be a bit resistant"},{"time":1096000,"text":"and not really to take it seriously."},{"time":1098000,"text":"So, you know, you've got to actually do your homework,"},{"time":1100000,"text":"in order to understand whether this is true."}]},{"cues":[{"time":1101000,"text":"And we'll just end with a few things."},{"time":1103000,"text":"One thing is, you know, you'll be hearing from a guy in the next session"},{"time":1106000,"text":"who said some time ago that he could sequence the human genome in half no time,"},{"time":1110000,"text":"and everyone said, \"Well, it's obviously impossible.\""},{"time":1112000,"text":"And you know what happened."},{"time":1113000,"text":"So, you know, this does happen."},{"time":1117000,"text":"We have various strategies -- there's the Methuselah Mouse Prize,"},{"time":1119000,"text":"which is basically an incentive to innovate,"},{"time":1122000,"text":"and to do what you think is going to work,"},{"time":1125000,"text":"and you get money for it if you win."},{"time":1128000,"text":"There's a proposal to actually put together an institute."},{"time":1131000,"text":"This is what's going to take a bit of money."},{"time":1133000,"text":"But, I mean, look -- how long does it take to spend that on the war in Iraq?"},{"time":1136000,"text":"Not very long. OK."},{"time":1137000,"text":"(Laughter)"},{"time":1138000,"text":"It's got to be philanthropic, because profits distract biotech,"},{"time":1141000,"text":"but it's basically got a 90 percent chance, I think, of succeeding in this."},{"time":1145000,"text":"And I think we know how to do it. And I'll stop there."},{"time":1148000,"text":"Thank you."},{"time":1149000,"text":"(Applause)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":1154000,"text":"Chris Anderson: OK. I don't know if there's going to be any questions"},{"time":1157000,"text":"but I thought I would give people the chance."},{"time":1159000,"text":"Audience: Since you've been talking about aging and trying to defeat it,"},{"time":1163000,"text":"why is it that you make yourself appear like an old man?"},{"time":1167000,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":1171000,"text":"AG: Because I am an old man. I am actually 158."},{"time":1174000,"text":"(Laughter)"},{"time":1175000,"text":"(Applause)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":1178000,"text":"Audience: Species on this planet have evolved with immune systems"},{"time":1182000,"text":"to fight off all the diseases so that individuals live long enough to procreate."},{"time":1186000,"text":"However, as far as I know, all the species have evolved to actually die,"},{"time":1191000,"text":"so when cells divide, the telomerase get shorter, and eventually species die."},{"time":1196000,"text":"So, why does -- evolution has -- seems to have selected against immortality,"},{"time":1201000,"text":"when it is so advantageous, or is evolution just incomplete?"}]},{"cues":[{"time":1205000,"text":"AG: Brilliant. Thank you for asking a question"},{"time":1207000,"text":"that I can answer with an uncontroversial answer."},{"time":1209000,"text":"I'm going to tell you the genuine mainstream answer to your question,"},{"time":1212000,"text":"which I happen to agree with,"},{"time":1214000,"text":"which is that, no, aging is not a product of selection, evolution;"},{"time":1217000,"text":"[aging] is simply a product of evolutionary neglect."},{"time":1220000,"text":"In other words, we have aging because it's hard work not to have aging;"},{"time":1225000,"text":"you need more genetic pathways, more sophistication in your genes"},{"time":1227000,"text":"in order to age more slowly,"},{"time":1229000,"text":"and that carries on being true the longer you push it out."},{"time":1232000,"text":"So, to the extent that evolution doesn't matter,"},{"time":1237000,"text":"doesn't care whether genes are passed on by individuals,"},{"time":1239000,"text":"living a long time or by procreation,"},{"time":1242000,"text":"there's a certain amount of modulation of that,"},{"time":1244000,"text":"which is why different species have different lifespans,"},{"time":1247000,"text":"but that's why there are no immortal species."}]},{"cues":[{"time":1250000,"text":"CA: The genes don't care but we do?"}]},{"cues":[{"time":1252000,"text":"AG: That's right."}]},{"cues":[{"time":1254000,"text":"Audience: Hello. I read somewhere that in the last 20 years,"},{"time":1259000,"text":"the average lifespan of basically anyone on the planet has grown by 10 years."},{"time":1264000,"text":"If I project that, that would make me think"},{"time":1267000,"text":"that I would live until 120 if I don't crash on my motorbike."},{"time":1272000,"text":"That means that I'm one of your subjects to become a 1,000-year-old?"}]},{"cues":[{"time":1277000,"text":"AG: If you lose a bit of weight."},{"time":1279000,"text":"(Laughter)"},{"time":1282000,"text":"Your numbers are a bit out."},{"time":1285000,"text":"The standard numbers are that lifespans"},{"time":1288000,"text":"have been growing at between one and two years per decade."},{"time":1291000,"text":"So, it's not quite as good as you might think, you might hope."},{"time":1295000,"text":"But I intend to move it up to one year per year as soon as possible."}]},{"cues":[{"time":1298000,"text":"Audience: I was told that many of the brain cells we have as adults"},{"time":1301000,"text":"are actually in the human embryo,"},{"time":1303000,"text":"and that the brain cells last 80 years or so."},{"time":1305000,"text":"If that is indeed true,"},{"time":1307000,"text":"biologically are there implications in the world of rejuvenation?"},{"time":1310000,"text":"If there are cells in my body that live all 80 years,"},{"time":1313000,"text":"as opposed to a typical, you know, couple of months?"}]},{"cues":[{"time":1315000,"text":"AG: There are technical implications certainly."},{"time":1317000,"text":"Basically what we need to do is replace cells"},{"time":1321000,"text":"in those few areas of the brain that lose cells at a respectable rate,"},{"time":1324000,"text":"especially neurons, but we don't want to replace them"},{"time":1327000,"text":"any faster than that -- or not much faster anyway,"},{"time":1329000,"text":"because replacing them too fast would degrade cognitive function."},{"time":1333000,"text":"What I said about there being no non-aging species earlier on"},{"time":1336000,"text":"was a little bit of an oversimplification."},{"time":1338000,"text":"There are species that have no aging -- Hydra for example --"},{"time":1342000,"text":"but they do it by not having a nervous system --"},{"time":1344000,"text":"and not having any tissues in fact that rely for their function"},{"time":1346000,"text":"on very long-lived cells."}]}]}